### Research spinoffs 

Unsurprisingly, particle colliders are complex structures that require the design and development of new technologies. Oftentimes, the materials developed are created in collaboration with other industry partners, which lead to further developement and application for other fields.

For example, Marie Curie didn't know what future technologies would benefit from her research of natural radioactivity of certain elements, but all today's medical imaging techniques steam from her and her colleagues' research. Neither did Einstein did develop his theory of General Relativity expecting it to be used for the exact calibration of GPS devices. Fundamental research not only advances human knowledge, it enables the rise of new and advanced technologies.

